WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.759
Looking at a single verse of scripture is kind of a springboard into our message this

00:00:03.759 --> 00:00:08.399
evening, and really I'll be dealing with the entirety of the particular verse of scripture

00:00:08.399 --> 00:00:10.760
that we'll look at this evening.

00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:15.119
Psalm chapter number 50, as we look at this verse, and verse number 15 will be the verse

00:00:15.119 --> 00:00:17.200
that we'll be looking at this evening.

00:00:17.200 --> 00:00:21.719
Psalm 50 and verse number 15, it is my prayer that the verse of scripture that is before

00:00:21.719 --> 00:00:26.760
us will encourage and strengthen the people of God.

00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:30.879
I know that I've said often I am so thankful for the Word of God and the way in which God's

00:00:30.879 --> 00:00:37.799
Word can comfort us and can convict us, it strengthens us, and I was praying earlier

00:00:37.799 --> 00:00:43.240
this week and just thanking God for His Word, I seek to, I won't say every day of my life

00:00:43.240 --> 00:00:48.439
because there may be a day that I have forgotten or missed, but by the grace of God every day

00:00:48.439 --> 00:00:52.240
I seek to thank Him specifically for His Word.

00:00:52.240 --> 00:00:57.599
As I enter into my time of reading and I thank God for giving us His Word, and it's

00:00:57.599 --> 00:01:04.639
powerful and it's profitable, and I was thinking this week specifically how His Word is probing.

00:01:04.639 --> 00:01:10.519
That's a good thing, by the way, and it searches us and it reveals to us our condition and

00:01:10.519 --> 00:01:12.519
our need for Him.

00:01:12.519 --> 00:01:16.480
And this evening, as we look at this particular verse of scripture, I do believe that it will

00:01:16.480 --> 00:01:19.000
be a great source of encouragement for us.

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:23.559
We understand this evening that the Bible is full of instruction, and instruction is

00:01:23.559 --> 00:01:24.559
good.

00:01:24.559 --> 00:01:27.680
I'm thankful for instruction, but something that's interesting about instruction is that

00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:31.440
we need to take heed in order for it to really make a difference.

00:01:31.440 --> 00:01:36.599
And so you can have those instruction manuals, you buy that piece of equipment, you buy that

00:01:36.599 --> 00:01:41.760
piece of furniture, whatever it might be, and it comes with some assembly required,

00:01:41.760 --> 00:01:42.760
right?

00:01:42.760 --> 00:01:47.839
And there's some directions, and those directions, if utilized, can be helpful.

00:01:47.839 --> 00:01:53.879
I read recently, if you've ever purchased anything from Ikea, and maybe you have some

00:01:53.879 --> 00:02:00.599
thoughts about Ikea, I know that Pierre loves Ikea, and everything you buy from Ikea you

00:02:00.599 --> 00:02:02.639
need to put together, and all of these things.

00:02:02.639 --> 00:02:07.639
And so I read recently how the president of the company was having a birthday, and all

00:02:07.639 --> 00:02:11.479
of the employees wanted to be a blessing to him, and so they wanted to get him a cake,

00:02:11.479 --> 00:02:17.080
and so they got him some eggs and some flour and some, you know, and happy birthday.

00:02:17.080 --> 00:02:21.559
But the point, though, is that instructions are contained with something for the purpose

00:02:21.559 --> 00:02:24.320
of being read, for the purpose of being followed.

00:02:24.320 --> 00:02:28.800
We think about the Word of God being a book of instruction, and it is imperative that

00:02:28.800 --> 00:02:34.839
we take heed to the truth that is contained therein, and simply follow the instruction.

00:02:34.839 --> 00:02:39.160
If you're taking notes this evening from this verse of Scripture, I've titled the message

00:02:39.160 --> 00:02:42.399
The Day of Trouble, The Day of Trouble.

00:02:42.399 --> 00:02:46.160
Notice what the Bible says here in Psalm 50 and verse number 15.

00:02:46.160 --> 00:02:53.759
