00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:43.559
to know that we can call upon him as we look at the passage.

00:04:43.559 --> 00:04:49.200
I want you to first of all this evening consider with me the presence of trouble, the presence

00:04:49.200 --> 00:04:50.200
of trouble.

00:04:50.200 --> 00:04:54.640
And I don't believe that I have to spend a whole lot of time laboring on this point to

00:04:54.640 --> 00:05:00.279
get you to understand that trouble exists, that it's present in the lives of the people

00:05:00.279 --> 00:05:02.279
that walk upon the face of the earth.

00:05:02.279 --> 00:05:05.160
There are adversities and difficulties that we face.

00:05:05.160 --> 00:05:10.079
In fact, Job 14 and verse number 1 says, Man that is born of a woman is a few days and

00:05:10.079 --> 00:05:12.559
full of trouble.

00:05:12.559 --> 00:05:17.519
And the word trouble here in our text of Scripture, when it says in the day of trouble, it means

00:05:17.519 --> 00:05:21.959
distress, affliction, adversity, or tribulation.

00:05:21.959 --> 00:05:26.359
And I think about what David says, and in just a little while we'll visit Psalm 34.

00:05:26.359 --> 00:05:29.320
At this point you can just stay here, we'll get there in just a moment.

00:05:29.320 --> 00:05:35.839
