00:40:50.000 --> 00:40:54.420
God has extended this invitation that we're to call upon Him in the day of trouble and

00:40:54.420 --> 00:40:59.580
that He will deliver us and thou shalt glorify me, I ask this evening, if I'm not willing

00:40:59.580 --> 00:41:04.080
to glorify God about the greatest thing that He's ever delivered me from, what makes me

00:41:04.080 --> 00:41:08.580
think I'm going to go ahead and glorify God tomorrow when He delivers me from some temporal

00:41:08.580 --> 00:41:11.580
inconvenience, some minor trouble that I face?

00:41:11.580 --> 00:41:14.260
You understand what I'm saying this evening?

00:41:14.260 --> 00:41:18.460
Listen, I'm trying, the Holy Spirit of God is dealing with me as much as I hope He's

00:41:18.460 --> 00:41:20.580
dealing with you.

00:41:20.580 --> 00:41:25.020
Because the reality this evening is that there are times in which we have experienced

00:41:25.020 --> 00:41:31.480
deliverance from God outside of the salvation deliverance that we don't glorify Him.

00:41:31.480 --> 00:41:33.120
Maybe we explain it some other way.

00:41:33.120 --> 00:41:37.340
Maybe we get a little shy about saying it in front of our coworkers, about we know that

00:41:37.340 --> 00:41:40.780
these folks are lost, we know our neighbors aren't going to understand, and so maybe we

00:41:40.780 --> 00:41:44.220
don't glorify God the way that we should.

00:41:44.220 --> 00:41:48.740
I think if we'd get comfortable glorifying God for our salvation, it'd probably become

00:41:48.740 --> 00:41:55.420
a whole lot more natural to glorify God for deliverance day by day, honestly.

00:41:55.420 --> 00:41:59.420
We come to a place where we just say, I'm going to glorify Him.

00:41:59.420 --> 00:42:06.740
So when we are delivered, when we experience that deliverance, and I'm thankful to be redeemed

00:42:06.740 --> 00:42:12.780
this evening, but thinking about the deliverance of the difficulties from day by day, how is

00:42:12.780 --> 00:42:15.200
it that we're glorifying the Lord?

00:42:15.200 --> 00:42:17.220
How do we glorify Him?

00:42:17.220 --> 00:42:18.220
How do we praise Him?

00:42:18.220 --> 00:42:19.220
How do we magnify Him?

00:42:19.220 --> 00:42:21.380
How do we honor Him?

00:42:21.380 --> 00:42:23.540
Who do we tell?

00:42:23.540 --> 00:42:26.660
Who knows that we're glorifying God?

00:42:26.660 --> 00:42:30.660
How are the others hearing about it?

00:42:30.660 --> 00:42:34.100
Miss Joyce wasn't going to be here this evening, but I'm going to share this illustration.

00:42:34.100 --> 00:42:35.100
I hope you're okay with it.

00:42:35.100 --> 00:42:37.020
Miss Joyce was a number of years ago.

00:42:37.020 --> 00:42:42.580
Miss Joyce had a situation with some skin cancer on her face, and she had just prayed

00:42:42.580 --> 00:42:47.780
about it, and she knew that God had delivered her from it and took care of it.

00:42:48.340 --> 00:42:49.340
And what a great testimony.

00:42:49.340 --> 00:42:50.340
She goes to the doctor.

00:42:50.340 --> 00:42:51.340
She didn't want to go to the doctor.

00:42:51.340 --> 00:42:53.500
She didn't like going to the doctor, amen.

00:42:53.500 --> 00:42:59.060
And she went to the doctor, and the doctor kind of astounded, said, it's gone.

00:42:59.060 --> 00:43:00.060
She's like, I know.

00:43:00.060 --> 00:43:01.860
God healed me, but I came for you.

00:43:01.860 --> 00:43:09.900
That's what she said, to be able to testify to that doctor of the healing of God in her

00:43:09.900 --> 00:43:11.900
life.

00:43:11.900 --> 00:43:13.660
And I'm thankful for that testimony.

00:43:13.660 --> 00:43:15.340
What a blessing.

00:43:15.340 --> 00:43:20.860
In this evening, I just wonder how are we doing with this aspect of Psalm 50 and verse

00:43:20.860 --> 00:43:23.620
number 15 from two perspectives.

00:43:23.620 --> 00:43:27.620
How are we doing on calling upon Him in the day of trouble?

00:43:27.620 --> 00:43:33.820
We face trouble, and when we face difficulty and adversity, who is it that we call?

00:43:33.820 --> 00:43:37.420
What are the, you know, you think about the woman that was dealing with the issue of blood

00:43:37.420 --> 00:43:38.420
for 12 years.

00:43:38.420 --> 00:43:44.580
She spent all of her substance to try to get healed, and she heard about Jesus.

00:43:44.580 --> 00:43:48.580
The people were thronging Him, and she said, if I could just touch the hem of His garment.

00:43:48.580 --> 00:43:50.900
He says, who touched me?

00:43:50.900 --> 00:43:54.100
Peter's like, what do you mean, who touched you?

00:43:54.100 --> 00:43:57.460
There's all kinds of people that are thronging you.

00:43:57.460 --> 00:43:59.460
Virtue has departed.

00:43:59.460 --> 00:44:02.220
Your faith has made you whole.

00:44:02.220 --> 00:44:06.820
And I just wonder this evening as we think about the, who is it that we call in the day

00:44:06.820 --> 00:44:07.820
of trouble?

00:44:07.820 --> 00:44:11.980
The God of the universe has given you an open invitation.

00:44:11.980 --> 00:44:18.340
And thou, excuse me, and call upon me in the day of trouble.

00:44:18.340 --> 00:44:20.420
I will deliver thee.

00:44:20.420 --> 00:44:23.700
And then here's the second aspect this evening of how are we doing.

00:44:23.700 --> 00:44:27.220
And thou shout glorify me.

00:44:27.220 --> 00:44:34.020
Oh, I trust this evening that we are honoring and exalting the name of our Savior in the

00:44:34.020 --> 00:44:35.020
way that we should.

00:44:35.020 --> 00:44:38.300
We started the service this evening, how appropriate.

00:44:38.300 --> 00:44:40.380
Praise Him, praise Him.

00:44:40.780 --> 00:44:44.500
Oh, God has done some amazing things for us.

00:44:44.500 --> 00:44:49.940
He has delivered you from the penalty of sin if you're His child this evening.

00:44:49.940 --> 00:44:56.020
And no doubt He has delivered you from many days of trouble upon this earth.

00:44:56.020 --> 00:44:58.600
And I'm so thankful for the deliverance of God.

00:44:58.600 --> 00:45:02.620
What a great promise and encouraging truth from the Word of God this evening.

00:45:02.620 --> 00:45:05.140
Oh, that we would glorify Him like we should.

00:45:05.140 --> 00:45:06.140
Let's pray tonight.

00:45:06.140 --> 00:45:07.780
Father, we love you.

00:45:07.780 --> 00:45:10.700
Thank you for loving us.

00:45:10.700 --> 00:45:15.380
Thank you for the simplicity of thy Word.

00:45:15.380 --> 00:45:17.820
Call upon me in the day of trouble.

00:45:17.820 --> 00:45:22.220
I will deliver thee and thou shalt glorify me.

00:45:22.220 --> 00:45:27.340
And I pray that we would call upon you in the day of trouble.

00:45:27.340 --> 00:45:30.300
If we'd be honest this evening, we're good at calling our friends.

00:45:30.300 --> 00:45:33.120
We're good at calling our parents.

00:45:33.120 --> 00:45:36.100
We're good at calling maybe a doctor.

00:45:36.100 --> 00:45:41.420
We're good at calling some advisor, some counselor.

00:45:41.420 --> 00:45:51.900
God, you are the omniscient, almighty God, our Father.

00:45:51.900 --> 00:45:55.900
And you said, call upon me.

00:45:55.900 --> 00:45:58.300
Help us, Lord.

00:45:58.300 --> 00:46:05.900
And Father, I pray that as we experience your deliverance in our lives, whatever that might

00:46:05.900 --> 00:46:13.500
look like, not always what we think it should look like, God, would you help us to glorify

00:46:13.500 --> 00:46:15.820
you?

00:46:15.820 --> 00:46:21.460
Would you help us, even as the psalmist says another part, let the redeemed of the Lord

00:46:21.460 --> 00:46:25.220
say so.

00:46:25.220 --> 00:46:32.540
Help us, Lord, in the day of trouble to call upon you and help us to be faithful to glorify

00:46:32.540 --> 00:46:33.540
you.

00:46:33.700 --> 00:46:37.060
I pray that you'd move and work as only you can, for it's in Christ's name we pray.

00:46:37.060 --> 00:46:37.500
Would you stand with us?

